snippet.textDisplay: Here in the States, the cost of scheduled maintenance and repairs are a consideration. A coworker had leased an Audi, then followed it with a MERC. He said he regretted the MERC because his out-of-pocket expenses were astronomical for the MERC compared to the Audi. At the time, MERC was second to none when it came to the white glove treatment the customer experienced when the car went to the shop, but since then, Audi has really stepped up their game in this area too. I drove VWs and the dealership I used also carried Audi so I also got to see the huge improvement in the customer service experience (though till not the insane level provided by several MERC dealerships in the Dallas, TX area).
